etymologies: late 18th century; earliest use found in John Bell. From sub- + crureus

definitions: A small muscle located under the vastus intermedius (crureus) muscle, originating from the femur and inserting into the suprapatellar bursa (also more fully "subcrureus muscle"). In early use also: †any of two or more bands of muscle forming this (obsolete).

notes.text: The preferred name for this muscle is now articularis genu.
